<item>
            <title>[CXF-6805] cxf-rt-transports-http adds Content-Type header to GET request</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-6805</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Then generating a web service client from WSDL the request sent to the server has an additional Content-Type header.  Microsoft IIS 6.0 fails to process these requests and returns 200-OK with empty body. &lt;br/&gt;
The Content-Type header should not be added to the http request when the method is GET.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12945262">CXF-6805</key>
            <summary>cxf-rt-transports-http adds Content-Type header to GET request</summary>
